  "issue_title": "fix(telegram): use AtomicU64 nonce so concurrent voice handlers can't collide on /tmp",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\n`rand_nonce()` in [crates/genie-core/src/telegram.rs](crates/genie-core/src/telegram.rs) sourced its \"unique\" tempfile suffix from `SystemTime::now().subsec_nanos()`. On Jetson Orin Nano the architected ARM generic timer runs at ~31.25 MHz, so `clock_gettime` has ~32 ns granularity \u2014 two callers in the same 32 ns window get identical nonces. The function's comment explicitly advertised collision-freedom under concurrent transcribes, but the implementation could not deliver it.\n\nTwo call sites are affected:\n\n- [telegram.rs:231](crates/genie-core/src/telegram.rs#L231) \u2014 voice-in download path (`/tmp/geniepod-tg-voice-<pid>-<nonce>.{ogg,wav}`)\n- [telegram.rs:325](crates/genie-core/src/telegram.rs#L325) \u2014 voice-out reply path (`/tmp/geniepod-tg-reply-<pid>-<nonce>.{ogg,wav}`)\n\nWhen two concurrent voice handlers collide, handler A's downloaded OGG can be overwritten by handler B mid-transcode \u2014 whisper-server receives the wrong audio and user A gets a transcript of user B's voice message.\n\n## Precedent\n\nCommit `65114f0` (issue #67) fixed exactly this class of race in `voice/stt.rs::transcribe_pcm` using a process-local `AtomicU64`. Its \"Out of scope\" note enumerated several other PID-only tempfile sites left for later but **did not list `telegram.rs:231` or `:325`** \u2014 those two sites were overlooked. The race is latent today (because `handle_update` still runs sequentially on `main`) but becomes load-bearing once concurrent spawning lands per issue #77, and is a bug against the function's stated contract either way.\n\n## Fix\n\nMirrors `voice::stt::TEMP_NONCE`: a `static AtomicU64` with `fetch_add(Ordering::Relaxed)`. Cannot collide within a process by construction, no syscall, no allocation.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] New `next_temp_nonce_is_unique_under_concurrent_callers` spawns 16 threads \u00d7 256 calls and asserts all 4096 returned nonces are distinct. Would have failed deterministically against the old `subsec_nanos`-based impl on a machine with coarse `clock_gettime` granularity (which Jetson is).\n- [x] `cargo test -p genie-core --lib telegram` \u2014 all 12 telegram tests pass (11 pre-existing + the new one).\n- [x] `cargo test --workspace` \u2014 green.\n- [x] `cargo clippy -p genie-core --all-targets -- -D warnings` \u2014 clean.\n- [x] `cargo check -p genie-core --no-default-features` \u2014 chat-only build (per PR #62 CI axis) still clean.\n\n## Related\n\n- Follow-up to #67 / commit `65114f0`, which fixed the same hazard in `voice/stt.rs` but did not extend coverage to the telegram tempfile sites.\n- Becomes load-bearing once concurrent `handle_update` spawning lands per #77.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-19T06:27:01.000Z",
